issue.title: Handle specific prime tower raft line spacing
issue.body:
Add the ability for a specific line spacing for the raft of the prime tower's first layer, because in some situations we want extra adhesion for it as it has a low footprint but can get very tall.

When the line spacing for the models raft is similar to the prime tower's raft, they are merged if too close. When they are different, the prime tower's raft take precedence.

CURA-11233

pull_request.title: [CURA-10783] prime tower with raft
pull_request.body:
# Description
This new feature adds a base to the prime tower and changes its adhesion:
* When using a raft, only the first layer of the raft is used for the prime tower
* It is now possible to add a base to the prime tower so that it can grow taller without risking breaking

# Technical changes
* Technically, the main difference is that the brim of the prime tower is no more handled by the brim algorithm, but by the tower generation itself, as it is now part of the base. For the raft, we use the classic raft generation for the first layer, then the prime tower handles its optional base and the rest of the raft ignores it.
* When the base of the prime tower overlaps with the models brim/raft, it takes precedence over them. This may be discussed to do it the other way.
* On the front-end side, the test of clearance areas on the first layer has been customized to ensure that the tower can be properly placed without causing troubles.

## Settings
* The setting "prime_tower_brim_enable" has been kept for easier retro-compatibility, however it now designates whether the prime tower has a base, not only a brim. It would make sense to rename it but that would require an upgrade script.
* The setting "prime_tower_base_size" has been added to customize it independantly from the model brim/raft width. However it default to the brim width.
* The setting "prime_tower_base_height" has been added to customize the height of the base. It defaults to the layer height, so that if you don't touch it, you get a brim-like base.
* The setting "prime_tower_base_curve_magnitude" has been added to allow customizing the shape of the base, which would depend on the used materials and actual height of the prime tower. Default value has been set to something that looks good for most situation, but may change with further tests.

## Retro-compatibility
Loading previous models with these new settings should give similar results, as the setting "prime_tower_brim_enable" is reused and the "prime_tower_base_size" defaults to "brim_width". The only situation that could cause problems is one where the prime tower was located very close to the model, with a brim. With the new implementation, the tower's brim is included in the disallowed area (because it may have a base) so it could overlap with the model and not allow slicing. This point can be discussed as a possible improvement.

# Tests
I have tested and fixed various positions of the prime tower and settings, including ooze shield and draft shield that overlap with the prime tower. One-at-a-time mode is not available in multi-extruders so no troubles here :)
Some other options/settings may be further tested to make sure that they are not impacted by the tower's base.
